cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of virtual environments to design biologically inspired robots. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of visual stimuli in virtual environments to study animal behavior. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category as the paper discusses the use of animal behavior studies to inform the design of multi-agent artificial intelligence. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of virtual environments to create immersive experiences for animals. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the use of virtual environments to study sensory-motor control in animals, which has implications for human-computer interaction.
